The paper discusses the use of machine learning for malware detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of adversarial modifications to test the robustness of these systems, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also touches on the need for these systems to adapt to novel attacks, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE) and system security (cs.SI).
